parameters.text:
Performing a mixed combination of spells correctly three times has a 10% chance of dropping Mystery Goo. However, performing the SAME correct 
magic three times in a row raises that chance to 20% and causes an Arts item to drop. Youll need one of each type of Arts to obtain Goofys 
Dream Shield from Merlin.

Every location (except Treehouse and Undersea Cave) can also perform the Fire, Blizzard, or Thunder actions. 
However, the Red Room and Lotus Forest will spawn mushrooms that exclusively perform those three actions.

Stop Arts will only drop from the ones Below Deck in Atlantica, the other 2 spots spawn Pink Agaricus.

Additionally, the End of the World zone can spawn every type of mushroom in the room right before Final Rest.

parameters.text:
\{How Heartless Spawning Works: \}
Heartless will stay dead once defeated until you go two doorways/maps away. However, keep in mind that some maps have multiple spawn tables that 
can happen (for example white mushrooms). You only need to go one doorway/map away to make spawns have a chance at flipping. What I'm saying 
is you don't need to clear out the room if you want to just switch what's spawning, just run in and out until you get what you want.

\{The Impact of Hallow Bastion 1st Visit / Point of No Return: \} 
After the first Hallow Bastion visit is completed, all the worlds will change they're heartless, it's recommended to farm materials prior to the
swap due to how much easier it is to find all the heartless types you need. You can start Hallow Bastion for access to the Darkball, Defender, 
Wyvern, Wizard, and Stealth Soldier spawns AS LONG AS YOU DON'T COMPLETE THE STORY THERE. Your safe until the SECOND Riku fight, this comes after 
defeating Malifecent's dragon form. The first Riku fight is fine to do (and nessecary to leave) it will give you back Donald, Goofy, and unlock
White Trinitys. Your safe all the way up to the Castle Chapel save point directly after beating Malifecent. The heartless in Olympus's cups also 
scale up in health after the switch, making it harder for the trials. Thankfully the mini-boss/secret heartless will still spawn after the change, 
so at least those ones can be farmed at any time.

\{Upgrades to Traverse Town Shops: \} 
The three shops in Traverse Town (item shop, acessory shop, and cid's gummi shop) will upgrade twice in the storyline, offering better items as 
you get further into the game. The first time is after sealing the keyhole in Agrabah. The second time is after completing the first Hallow 
Bastion visit. 

Note that after the second/final upgrade to the shops you can buy Orichalcum from the item shop for 5k each. So technically you don't need to 
worry about finding Orichalcums in treasure chests if your willing to wait until late game to use them (although I think getting as many of the
treasure chest ones as you can while your getting through the story is a much faster and better use of your time/gold).

parameters.text:
\{Jump Casting Magic: \} 
Casting magic while airborn is a pretty strong technique. This allows most of your magic attacks to have a faster startup and end lag animation, 
allowing for much faster casts. There is only 3 magic that I do not reccomend doing it for, Fire, Cure, and Aero. Fire already has a quick 
animation and is the only magic with a rapid-fire on the ground. Cure and Aero are just riskier to do airborn because if you land before the 
animation finishes the effect will not occur. You CAN jump cast them but without high jump its a very precise jump/timing, and with high jump its 
still very easy to mess up (however the mp will not be used if this happens at least). All other magic though I would recommend jump casting.  

\{Oogie's Manor Disappearing: \} 
After defeating Oogie's final form the Manor completely disappears. But thankfully most, if not all, the treasure chests in that area that you
missed are relocated to the ruins / ground level of where the manor stood. I'm not certain if its every single chest but all the important ones 
will have new locations. 

\{The Sorta Broken Red Trinity: \} 
There is a Red Trinity at the ground level of Oogie's Manor that is difficult to activate sometimes. First off, if your familiar with the 
original ps2 version of kh1 this trinity has been moved due to it being possible to miss it entirely after the manor was destroyed. Thankfully 
in the final mix / 1.5 versions of the game it's been moved to an archway. However some whacky things still happen with this mark in the newer 
versions of the game. The easiest way to explain it is there is two different spawn types that can happen in this area. You could get the normal
heartless spawn, or the Chimera spawn (appears after killing a few). If you get the NORMAL spawn, the red trinity symbol will be showing on the
archway wall regardless if it has been collected or not, this is a visual bug. However in the normal spawn scenario not only is it visually 
bugged, but you cannot get the prompt to use it. The fix for this is to get the other spawn, the CHIMERA spawn. When Chimera is defeated the 
prompt to use it will become available. The cool thing about this bug though, is once the trinity has been used, it will still show up visually
on only the normal spawn encounters. What this means is if your farming out your Blazing Stones from Chimera, you can use this as an indicator 
for if he will spawn or not. Showing after already used = No Chimera.

parameters.text:
\{Free Potions & Elixirs: \} 
After you add your second Torn Page to 100 Acre Wood, you can get free Elixirs and Potions from Rabbit's garden by plucking his cabbage and 
pumpkins (2% chance for elixir, 8% for potion). Although somewhat tedious.

\{Hercules Time Trial Exploit: \}
For some reason the game is programmed to pause your timer if you pause and hit reset while fighting Hercules, making the time trial much
easier. You still need to REACH Hercules before time runs out though before activating it (so the first 9 waves). 

\{Geppetto's House: \}
Once Monstro is cleared, Geppetto's house will spawn in District 1 of Traverse Town. Geppetto gives you gummi ship blueprints based on how
many heartless have been defeated. The intervals are 0, 500, 1000, 1500, 3000, 4000, and 5000. The 5000 one has an added requirement of having
all 6 summons acquired. You'll know if you received them all from Geppetto if he gives you the Hyperion blueprint. Pinocchio will also give you
the Chocobo blueprint for entering and leaving the house 30 times. 

\{Aero Beneficial Oversight?: \}
When you cast the spell Aero, if an enemy hits you and interrupts the animation, the effect still goes off. This isn't a huge deal but still
a nice little thing to know. No more panic casting.

\{EXP Zero Buff: \}
If you have EXP Zero equipped, not only does it stop you from leveling up, it also has two hidden abilities. You cannot be one-shot by an attack
as long as you are above 1 health, and your damage output scales higher on any enemy that has more than 300 health (so basically just bosses). 
The reason this is important, is you can still equip the ability for it's hidden benefits at level 100, making you stronger than normal.

parameters.text:
\{Requirements For Secret Ending: \}
There are two different secret ending variations. Basically a standard one, and an extended cut one. The requirements for unlocking them change
depending on what difficulty you are playing the game on.

Beginner:
You simply cannot achieve either secret ending on this mode. 

Final Mix (Standard/Normal):
The easier ending you just need to seal all the keyholes (including 100 acre wood) and find all 99 dalmatians. 
The extended ending you need the same as above but with the added requirement of having a completed journal. You can tell if the journal is 
complete by a yellow Micky Mouse symbol appearing next to it on the pause menu. A completed journal basically means you did everything in 
the game. You must see all characters and heartless, collect all Ansem reports, find all puppies, do every trinity mark, and play every 
mini-game at least once. 

Proud (Hard Mode):
The requirements are actually dialed back a bit on proud mode. The easier ending you just need to complete the game. 
The extended ending you need to seal all the keyholes (again, including 100 acre wood), and complete the Hades Cup. You do not need to do the
solo or time trial versions of Hades Cup.

You can tell which ending you got from the name of it when it plays. 
The standard secret ending is called "Another Side, Another Story"
The extended version is called "Another Side, Another Story [Deep Dive]"
